 MBOMBELA – An nationwide bus strike will take place tomorrow. According to recent reports, unions have given notice of a strike to the South African Road Passengers Bargaining Council following a deadlock in wage negotiations. Also read: CIT heists on the increase in the Lowveld
 
A spokesman for Buscor in Mbombela said that they are not sure if they will be affected. “We do not know if our bus drivers are going to strike are not. We will have to wait and see.” Please be aware that this might affect your transport arrangements tomorrow morning, as you might not be able to take the bus to your destination. Also read:  VIDEO: CIT robbers hit Fidelity vehicle in Mbombela